  "summary": "Malicious code in chalk-pro (npm)",
  "details": "Combosquat package \"chalk-pro\" mimicking the popular chalk terminal library. On postinstall, it spawns a detached background Node.js process (outlives the npm install) that fetches second-stage code from hxxps://www[.]jsonkeeper[.]com/b/TOAAK and executes it via new Function(\"require\", r.data.cookie)(require) — full remote code execution with the Node.js require() scope available. A 262KB hex-encoded file is bundled as \"LICENSE\" alongside, providing additional payload material for the remote stage. the author and copyright fields are spoofed from other projects (nodemailer, chalk).",
